race.comment: DARTS DALY (5) returned from a spell when he was beaten 2.2L over 1200m at Mornington. Has been in the money at each second up start. Improver with strong each-way prospects. ARCANDAM (6) returned from a break and proved too good scoring by 1L over 1200m at Murray Bridge in a 68. The speedy galloper is further improved and Kersley is aboard today and that's a positive switch. He has upside and stripping fitter will give a big sight.  STORMBENDER (14) positions forward and improved narrowly beaten in a CL1 at Cranbourne. Sits down in the weights and Yendall is aboard today. DELIVERING (1) resumes for the premier stable and has jumped out well. May need one, but the 4kg claim brings him right into it.
